modules.description: Provides operations to iterate over and transform a collection of values of type `t`, including retrieving all elements as a list. Works with any data type wrapped in the `t` abstraction. Used to generate a complete list of items for processing or output in a pipeline.

Generates a list of all possible values for a finite type using a ppx rewriter. It operates on types annotated with `[@@deriving enumerate]`, producing a predefined list of instances. This is useful for exhaustive pattern matching or generating test cases based on type definitions.

Provides operations to iterate over and transform collections of values, converting them into lists for processing. It works with any data type wrapped in the `t` abstraction, enabling pipeline-based manipulation. Functions include mapping, filtering, and folding over elements. For example, it can generate a list of all items from a structured data source or apply a transformation to each element in a sequence.

Provides a function to generate enumeration values for types annotated with the `[@@deriving enumerate]` attribute. Works with OCaml types that have been extended with custom rewriters to produce sequential values. Used to automatically create a list of all possible instances of a type for testing or serialization.
